The paper deals with a discrete system of entities residing on a two-dimensional square grid, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for transforming one shape into another. The use of a pushing mechanism suggests a robotics and control perspective (cs.RO), while the focus on the geometry of the grid and the shapes involved suggests a computational geometry perspective (cs.CG). The concept of programmable matter also suggests a focus on self-organizing systems and swarm intelligence (cs.SI), while the study of the efficiency of the transformations suggests a focus on complexity theory and algorithms (cs.CC).
